hared/News2001/MoonLanding/moon-earth.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Supporting the poor: should we have to? </span><hr size=1> In response to the post regarding government redistribution of wealth:<br>
<br>
There are 2 reasons why we would support Socialism, but not donate extra money to the IRS today.<br>
<br>
a)  We have a capitalist regime in power today.  Giving extra money to a capitalist governement is NOT the same as giving money to a socialist regime.  If I gave extra money, in fact, 75% of my money, to the IRS, and they bought my food, clothes, utilities, etc..., I'd be happy.  Even if 5% of that went to support outright leechers.  But this extra money only goes to help the poor.  Not to pay for my life.<br>
<br>
b) Bush and his budget. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uewanakanach0king.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ewan aka nach0king</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/28/02 5:52:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7432.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.seiryuu.org/~suikoden/Navigation/soul_s.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Supporting the poor: should we have to? </span><hr size=1> BTW, I'm just clarifying my standpoint regarding duty, in case anyone was bothered by it. I mean, I feel it someone is *truly* destitute and in need, we have a moral duty to help them. If they are in such dire straits that they might starve/die/whatever. But it is not the responsibility of the Government to do so. It should be a personal choice, but I feel one everyone SHOULD make to help the very, very poor and destitute. But not the lazy. They can @#%$ try harder. <p><p><b><font face="Tahoma" size="5"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48384">Jokah Pandahunter</a><br>
